---
import AccordionItem from './AccordionItem.astro';
---

{/* FAQ */}
<div class="mx-auto max-w-[85rem] px-4 py-10 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 lg:py-14" id="faq">
  {/* Title */}
  <div class="mx-auto mb-10 max-w-2xl text-center lg:mb-14">
    <h2
      class="text-dark text-3xl font-bold md:text-4xl md:leading-tight 2xl:text-5xl dark:text-stone-100"
    >
      Got Questions? Get Answers
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-1 text-stone-600 2xl:text-lg dark:text-stone-400">
      Answers to the most frequently asked questions.
    </p>
  </div>
  {/* End Title */}

  <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl">
    {/* Accordion */}
    <div class="hs-accordion-group">
      <AccordionItem
        id="hs-basic-with-title-and-arrow-stretched-heading-one"
        collapseId="hs-basic-with-title-and-arrow-stretched-collapse-one"
        heading="How do I find a recipe on OpenStove?"
        isActive={true}
      >
        Just head over to the 'Recipes' page. You can browse through the curated
        collection or use our search functionality to find something specific.
        Whether you're after a comfort food classic or a daring new dish, our
        library is at your fingertips.
      </AccordionItem>

      <AccordionItem
        id="hs-basic-with-title-and-arrow-stretched-heading-two"
        collapseId="hs-basic-with-title-and-arrow-stretched-collapse-two"
        heading="How can I contribute a recipe to OpenStove?"
      >
        The easiest way is our
        <a
          class="focus-visible:ring-secondary rounded-md font-medium whitespace-nowrap underline decoration-2 underline-offset-2 hover:text-stone-600 focus:outline-hidden focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:outline-hidden dark:hover:text-stone-400"
          href="/contribute"
        >
          online contribution form
        </a>
        – no Git required. Prefer the open-source workflow? Submit a pull request
        through our
        <a
          class="focus-visible:ring-secondary rounded-md font-medium whitespace-nowrap underline decoration-2 underline-offset-2 hover:text-stone-600 focus:outline-hidden focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:outline-hidden dark:hover:text-stone-400"
          href="https://github.com/mearashadowfax/OpenStove"
          target="_blank"
        >
          GitHub repository
        </a>
        following the Markdown recipe format. Maintainers review submissions and add
        licensed photos separately (photos are not stored in the public repo).
      </AccordionItem>

      <AccordionItem
        id="hs-basic-with-title-and-arrow-stretched-heading-three"
        collapseId="hs-basic-with-title-and-arrow-stretched-collapse-three"
        heading="Is coding knowledge required for contributing?"
      >
        No. Use the
        <a
          class="focus-visible:ring-secondary rounded-md font-medium whitespace-nowrap underline decoration-2 underline-offset-2 hover:text-stone-600 focus:outline-hidden focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:outline-hidden dark:hover:text-stone-400"
          href="/contribute"
        >
          contribute form
        </a>
        to share a recipe without touching code. Git and Markdown remain available
        for contributors who prefer pull requests – our guidelines walk you through
        that path too.
      </AccordionItem>

      <AccordionItem
        id="hs-basic-with-title-and-arrow-stretched-heading-four"
        collapseId="hs-basic-with-title-and-arrow-stretched-collapse-four"
        heading="Can I save my favorite recipes?"
      >
        Absolutely! You can bookmark your favorite recipes for quick access
        during your future visits. Just click the bookmark icon on any recipe
        page to save it. All your bookmarked recipes will be available under the
        'Saved Recipes' section, which you can view anytime. Your favorites are
        saved locally in your browser, so there's no need for an account or
        sign-up.
      </AccordionItem>

      <AccordionItem
        id="hs-basic-with-title-and-arrow-stretched-heading-five"
        collapseId="hs-basic-with-title-and-arrow-stretched-collapse-five"
        heading="What makes OpenStove different from other recipe websites?"
      >
        OpenStove is a no-nonsense, zero-ad recipe database that's powered by
        the culinary community. It's all about the content – crisp, clear, and
        straight to the plate. Plus, our open-source approach means anyone can
        contribute and access recipes without any commercial gatekeeping.
      </AccordionItem>

      <AccordionItem
        id="hs-basic-with-title-and-arrow-stretched-heading-six"
        collapseId="hs-basic-with-title-and-arrow-stretched-collapse-six"
        heading="Is OpenStove free to use?"
      >
        Yes, OpenStove is completely free and accessible to everybody. There are
        no hidden fees or premium content – our goal is to make cooking
        knowledge universally available.
      </AccordionItem>
    </div>
  </div>
  {/* End Accordion */}
</div>
{/* End FAQ*/}
